definition: to sign one's name/visa/variant of 籤|签[qian1]
inscribed bamboo stick (used in divination, gambling, drawing lots etc)/small wood sliver/label/tag

sentences.english: Need toothpicks to keep your eyes open at work?

sentences.english: The tiger needs a toothpick to pick his teeth.

sentences.english: Would you please pass the toothpicks?

sentences.english: Each sculpture was made from only one toothpick.

sentences.english: Carry some cinnamon-flavored toothpicks with you.

sentences.english: There's also a tweezer and toothpick and a hole for lanyard attachment.
